Position: HIS Business Intelligence Data Analyst
Program: Health Information Systems
Department: Health Services
Reports To: HIS Business Intelligence Manager
Compensation: $38.46 per hour
Status: 100%, Full-Time, Non-Exempt, Confidential
Probation: 90 days
Benefits: Medical, Vision, Dental, and Life Insurance; also including Long-Term Disability, an Employee Assistance Program, and a 403(b)-retirement plan

JOB SUMMARY: The Health Information Systems (HIS) Unit provides software and hardware support to the Health Services (HS) Department of the Los Angeles LGBT Center (Center). HIS administrates and supports all health information systems including the Electronic Health Record (EHR), Pharmacy Management Software, and all supporting/ancillary software applications to support the mission of HS. This position will provide Business Intelligence support to the financial and clinical operations of the Center and is responsible for collecting, scrubbing, and extracting data from various sources to generate reports, dashboards, and analytical solutions. The position will routinely perform and manage standard and advance reporting/analytics and derive insights to drive business decisions and operations. The position will be responsible to manage and maintain accurate, complete, and timely routine reports/analysis and to prepare ad-hoc reports/analysis in understanding and support of business initiatives. The Business Intelligence Analyst will also assist in the design and development of healthcare data feeds, interfaces, SQL Server Data Warehouses and other related needs.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
1) Supports the buildout of the Analytics and Reporting platform;
2) Creates clear reporting on requested business metrics using Tableau and other reporting tools;
3) Designs, develops and maintains custom reports using SQL programming, SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS);
4) Uses data visualization, data manipulation, and pattern recognition to support problem resolution;
5) Extracts, analyzes, and interprets healthcare and/or financial data to address business needs;
6) Performs analysis on healthcare data using problem-solving and analytical skills, correlates with business processes and assists management by developing solutions to business issues;
7) Collaborates with leadership to provide meaningful and credible feedback on reporting capabilities and needs;
8) Conducts routine data validation and identifies ways to improve data reliability, efficiency, and quality;
9) Participates in development and deployment of Tableau reports;
10) Participates in formal training classes, conferences and self-instruction as needed;
11) Creates supporting documentation that can be referenced by business stakeholders;
12) Other duties as assigned;

JOB QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE:
1) Knowledge of or experience working with the LGBTQ community and familiarity with issues of relevance to LGBTQ people;
2) A passion for the Center’s work and its mission to make the world a better place for LGBTQ people;
3) Undergraduate in engineering, Data Analysis, Mathematics, Statistics or Computer Science (Master’s preferred);
4) 2-3 years industry experience in IT relational databases and SQL reporting;
5) 2-3 years of increasingly complex experience in quantifying, measuring, and analyzing financial/performance management metrics;
6) Working knowledge with EHR clinical workflows and Practice Management systems preferred;
7) Knowledge of data warehousing and business intelligence platforms;
8) Highly analytical with ability to translate complex information into simpler terms and concepts;
9) Experience creating SQL queries from scratch (including complex stored procedures) and data processes;
10) Intermediate knowledge with data reporting tools Tableau, SSRS, Excel and Access;
11) Working knowledge on SSIS;
12) Ability to maintain confidentiality;
13) Ability to pay attention to little things and ensure tasks and assignments are completed in timely and appropriate manner;
14) Demonstrated ability to work effectively with people of diverse races, ethnicities, nationalities, sexual orientations, gender identities, gender expression, socio-economic backgrounds, religions, ages, English-speaking abilities, immigration status, and physical abilities in a multicultural environment.

The Los Angeles LGBT Center is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to fostering diversity within its staff. Applications are encouraged from all persons regardless of their race, color, ancestry, religious creed, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, medical/physical/mental condition, pregnancy/childbirth and related medical condition, age, marital status, or veteran status.
